de.oaam.model.oaam.mapping

Interface Schedule

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ElementA, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ModeDependentElementA, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, VariantDependentElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ScheduleImpl

    public interface Schedule
extends ElementA, ModeDependentElementA, VariantDependentElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Schedule'. A schedule assigens periodic or non-periodic time slots to a task assignment.

    The following features are supported:

    • Rate
    • Is Periodic
    • Priority
    • Scheduled Times
    See Also:
    MappingPackage.getSchedule()

      • getRate

        double getRate()
        Returns the value of the 'Rate' attribute. The default value is "0.0". The execution rate of periodic tasks in [Hz]. Non-periodic tasks shall have a rate of 0.

        the value of the 'Rate' attribute.

      • getPriority

        int getPriority()
        Returns the value of the 'Priority' attribute. The default value is "0". Higher values mean higher priority. Higher priority tasks are calculated before others in the same time slot in case of preemptive sheduling.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Priority' attribute.
        See Also:
        setPriority(int), MappingPackage.getSchedule_Priority()

        Returns the value of the 'Scheduled Times' containment reference list. The list contents are of type ScheduledTime. All active times of this schedule.
